Uses of Package
com.samskivert.depot

  • Packages that use com.samskivert.depot 
    Package Description
    com.samskivert.depot
    The bulk of the Depot public API.
    com.samskivert.depot.clause
    Models the clauses of a SQL query: where, join, limit, etc.
    com.samskivert.depot.expression
    Contains the API by which SQL expressions are created.
    com.samskivert.depot.operator
    Operators that cannot be created via the fluent API.
    com.samskivert.depot.util
    Various utilities.
  • Classes in com.samskivert.depot used by com.samskivert.depot 
    Class and Description
    CacheAdapter
    Implementations of this interface are responsible for all the caching needs of Depot.
    CacheAdapter.CacheCategory 
    CacheAdapter.CachedValue
    The encapsulated result of a cache lookup.
    CacheInvalidator
    Implementors of this interface performs perform cache invalidation for calls to DepotRepository.updatePartial(com.samskivert.depot.Key<T>, com.samskivert.depot.expression.ColumnExp<?>, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object...) and DepotRepository.deleteAll(java.lang.Class<T>, com.samskivert.depot.clause.WhereClause).
    CacheKey
    This interface uniquely identifies a single persistent entry for caching purposes.
    CountRecord
    Handy record for computing the count of something.
    DatabaseException
    Represents a failure reported by the underlying database.
    DataMigration
    Encapsulates a migration of data between entities that should be run only once and using the same safeguards applied to entity migrations.
    DepotRepository.CacheStrategy 
    EHCacheAdapter.EHCacheConfig 
    EHCacheAdapter.EHCachePerformance 
    Key
    A special form of WhereClause that uniquely specifies a single database row and thus also a single persistent object.
    KeySet
    Contains a set of primary keys that match a set of persistent records.
    PersistenceContext
    Defines a scope in which global annotations are shared.
    PersistenceContext.CacheListener
    A cache listener is notified when cache entries change.
    PersistenceContext.CacheTraverser
    The callback for PersistenceContext.cacheTraverse(java.lang.Class<? extends com.samskivert.depot.PersistentRecord>, com.samskivert.depot.PersistenceContext.CacheTraverser<T>); this is called for each entry in a given cache.
    PersistenceContext.CanMigrate
    Used by PersistenceContext.PersistenceContext(CanMigrate).
    PersistentRecord
    The base class for all persistent records used in Depot.
    Query
    The root of a fluent mechanism for constructing queries.
    SchemaMigration
    Encapsulates the migration of a persistent record's database schema.
    SQLFragment
    Represents a fragment of an SQL statement, generally a clause (WHERE, FROM, ...) or an expression (1+1, 'foo', "columnName", ...).
    Stats.Snapshot
    An immutable class used to report statistics on repository activity.
    Transformer
    Transforms a persistent record field into a format that can be read and written by the underlying database.
    ValidatingCacheInvalidator
    An augmented cache invalidator interface for invalidators that can ensure that they are operating on the proper persistent record class.
